               <p>BENJAMIN BURGAR. I am a <rs id="t18251208-77-viclabel385" type="occupation">draper and salesman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18251208-77-victim457 t18251208-77-viclabel385"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18251208-77-crimeloc386">Hospital-row, Chelsea</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18251208-77-crimeloc386" type="placeName" value="Hospital-row, Chelsea"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18251208-77-crimeloc386" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18251208-77-off383 t18251208-77-crimeloc386"></join>. Charlotte Ashton came to my shop on the 14th of November, about three o'clock, and pointed out the prisoner as having taken a pair of boots from my door. I followed, and found them on him- I had seen them safe on the story post of my door, about half an hour before - he asked me to forgive him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18251208-77-person458">
                  CHARLOTTE 
                  ASHTON
               <interp inst="t18251208-77-person458" type="surname" value="ASHTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18251208-77-person458" type="given" value="CHARLOTTE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18251208-77-person458" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner cut the boots away from the door, and put them under his arm - he walked away, in company with another boy. I went, and told Mr. Burgar, who took him with them.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18251208-77-person459">
